model_content:
{
  "passage_id": "POE_WORKS_VOLUME_1_009",
  "condition": "paraphrase",
  "rewritten_text": "I feared that the persistent weight of adversity had finally disturbed my companion’s sanity. Consequently, I resolved without delay to join the black man. Upon arriving at the dock, I observed a scythe and a trio of shovels, all seemingly brand new, resting inside the vessel we were to board. “What is the purpose of these, Jup?” I asked. “That’s a scythe, master, and a spade.” “Quite right; but why are they here?” “They are the tools Master Will insisted I purchase for him in town, and I had to pay a devil of a price for them.” “But what, in the name of all that is strange, does your ‘Master Will’ intend to do with scythes and shovels?” “That is more than I can say, and I’ll be damned if I don’t think it’s more than he knows, too. But it all comes down to the bug.” Realizing I would gain no clarity from Jupiter, whose mind seemed entirely consumed by “the bug,” I boarded the boat and set off. A steady, favorable wind carried us quickly to the small inlet north of Fort Moultrie, and a two-mile trek led us to the cabin. We reached our destination around three in the afternoon. Legrand had been waiting for us with intense anticipation. He seized my hand with a nervous intensity that unsettled me and confirmed my growing fears. His face was deathly pale, and his sunken eyes shone with a strange, feverish brightness. After asking about his well-being, I inquired, unsure of what else to say, if he had secured the scarabæus from Lieutenant G——. “Oh, yes,” he answered, flushing deeply, “I retrieved it from him the following morning. Nothing could induce me to give up that scarabæus. Are you aware that Jupiter is entirely correct about it?” “In what sense?” I questioned, feeling a heavy sense of dread. “In believing it to be a beetle of genuine gold.” He spoke with such intense gravity that I was profoundly disturbed. “This insect will secure my fortune,” he added with a victorious grin, “and restore my family’s estate. Is it any surprise that I value it so highly? Since Fate has seen fit to grant it to me, I need only utilize it correctly to reach the gold it points toward. Jupiter, fetch me that scarabæus!” “What! The bug, master? I would rather not bother that bug—you must get it yourself.” Legrand then stood with a solemn, dignified manner and retrieved the beetle for me from a glass display case. It was a stunning scarabæus, unknown to science at the time—naturally a significant discovery from a biological perspective. It featured two circular, dark spots near one end of its back, and a single elongated one near the other. Its shell was exceptionally hard and lustrous, appearing exactly like polished gold. The insect’s weight was quite extraordinary, and, all things considered, I could scarcely fault Jupiter for his assessment; yet, I could not for the life of me understand why Legrand agreed with him."
}

