ach the gold it points toward. Jupiter, bring me that beetle!\" \"What! The bug, master? I’d rather not bother that bug—you must get it yourself.\" Legrand then stood up with a grave, stately air and brought me the beetle from the glass case where it was kept. It was a beautiful specimen, unknown to naturalists at the time, and certainly a great scientific prize. There were two round, black spots near one end of its back and a long one near the other. The scales were extremely hard and glossy, looking exactly like polished gold. The insect was remarkably heavy, and considering everything, I could hardly blame Jupiter for his opinion; however, I could not for the life of me understand why Legrand agreed with him."
