es retract, and the insect is free to depart, according to the Reverend P. Keith’s System of Physiological Botany. Since their inception, bees have built their honeycombs with specific sides, quantities, and angles that, as proven by complex mathematical analysis, provide the maximum storage capacity while ensuring the greatest structural integrity. Late in the eighteenth century, mathematicians debated how to calculate the optimal shape for windmill sails based on their varying distances from the rotating vanes and the center of motion. This remains a highly intricate challenge, essentially requiring the determination of the ideal configuration across an infinite number of points and distances along the arm."
